examples.en: I phoned my mum straight away.
He's phoned me several times today.
I phoned the bank to cancel the cheque.
I phoned the hotel to cancel my reservation.
If he hasn't phoned in a week, I'll phone him.
I swallowed my pride and phoned him.
I phoned him up and got a crossed line.
Derek felt slighted when no one phoned him back.
Stevie phoned to say that he was going to be late.
She phoned her friend to invite her over for dinner.
When I got home I phoned Jo to catch up on all the gossip.
Well, she could at least have phoned to say she wasn't coming!
'You could have just phoned.' 'I wanted to explain things face to face.'
I phoned the bank and asked them to stop the cheque (=not pay a cheque that I had written).
I phoned him twice on Friday and left messages, but he never returned my call (=he didn't phone me).
